  "response_text": "A white Febreze logo appears centered against a bright blue sky with soft clouds. The scene moves to a sunny front garden outside a neat white house. An adult woman with short, curly dark hair walks along the path toward the door. She wears a dark blazer over a light blue shirt, loose brown trousers, and carries a dark bag over one shoulder. The small garden is full of potted plants and flowers, with ivy climbing the wall, a bench near the window, and other houses visible beyond a hedge.\n\nAs she approaches, the front door comes into view. Its design looks almost like a smiling face: two round windows near the top resemble eyes, a circular door knocker sits like a nose, and a curved mail slot forms a smile. The woman pauses in front of it, facing the door, while sunlight casts leafy shadows across the white wall.\n\nInside the home, the woman stands just inside the entryway holding her dark jacket and bags. The cheerful door is now behind her, but the air around the room is filled with visible yellow-green, smoky odor clouds. One cloud surrounds a red sneaker floating near the ceiling, another hovers near the left side of the room, and another lingers by a plant and chair on the right. The woman looks around, then tilts her gaze upward toward the sneaker cloud with a concerned, wary expression.\n\nA product display appears on a bright, clean background: Febreze Plug packaging beside the Febreze logo. The package shows the white plug-in device and a refill labeled “Linen & Sky,” with a yellow badge reading “Fade Defy Plug.” The plug-in device is then shown close up as a white oval unit with a clear lower reservoir, plugged into a wall outlet. Beside it, blue circular-arrow graphics surround the words “FADE DEFY PLUG.” Another demonstration shows the plug-in on the wall releasing two pale blue streams upward, next to a blue graphic that reads “2 COMPLEMENTARY SCENTS.”\n\nBack in the entryway, the Febreze Plug is visible in an outlet on the right wall. Bright blue scent streams sweep through the room in broad, flowing bands, passing across the coat rack, shoes, plants, and front door area. The earlier yellow-green odor clouds remain visible at first, including the cloud around the sneaker and another around a small dog in a bed near the floor, but the blue waves visually take over the space.\n\nThe woman now appears in a different room wearing a teal-blue sweater. Blue scent streams and tiny sparkling particles move across the foreground. She looks upward and around with a softened, pleased expression. A large circular blue graphic beside her counts upward, changing from “UP TO 3 DAYS” to “11,” then “41,” and finally “UP TO 50 DAYS,” with small text at the bottom reading “*low setting.”\n\nThe final home scene is a cozy living room washed with blue freshness waves. A child with curly hair sits on a rug beside a large light-colored dog, petting or resting a hand on it. The woman relaxes on a sofa in the background. The room has soft furnishings, a coffee table with household items, plants, curtains, and warm lamps, giving it a calm, comfortable feel.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean blue background with Febreze Plug products arranged in a row. The front package again shows the white plug-in and “Linen & Sky” refill, with the yellow “Fade Defy” badge. Large white text reads “febreze PLUG,” and a small P&G logo appears in the upper right.",
